<HEADLINE>
FT  04 NOV 93 / Rates exemption for Scottish estates
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
OWNERS of Scottish estates will no longer have to pay non-domestic rates on
their deer forests, salmon rivers, grouse moors and other shooting, Mr Ian
Lang, Scottish secretary, said yesterday.
In a parliamentary answer he said that sporting rights would be exempted
from non-domestic rates from 1995, bringing Scotland into line with England
and Wales.
