<HEADLINE>
FT  04 NOV 93 / Arrest warrant for Brazilian
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A WARRANT has been issued for the arrest of Mr Paulo Cesar Farias, the man
allegedly at the centre of a multi-million dollar corrupt fund-raising
scheme for Mr Fernando Collor, the disgraced Brazilian president.
The Brazilian embassy in London said yesterday that a warrant was issued
after the British government agreed to start extradition proceedings against
Mr Farias, Britain has no formal extradition treaty with Brazil.
The embassy said the case was not linked to that of Mr Ronald Biggs, who
escaped from Wandsworth prison in 1965 after being convicted of the August
1963 'great train robbery' and now lives with his son in Rio de Janeiro.
</TEXT>
