FT  04 NOV 93 / World Trade News: US tobacco ruling attacked
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PHILIP RAWSTORNE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   LONDON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
US legislation requiring the country's cigarette manufacturers to use at
least 75 per cent US-grown tobacco attacked yesterday by Mr Martin
Broughton, chief executive of BAT Industries, the UK tobacco and financial
services group, Philip Rawstorne writes in London. It was ' a flagrant
breach of Gatt rules' he said. Because of the move, BAT had closed its
tobacco leaf operations in Panama, which exported to the US, at a cost of
Pounds 7m in lost profits.
