as 3M and National Semiconductor, reported pre-tax profits of Pounds 2.98m
(Pounds 1.76m) for the year ended September and earnings per share of 7.4p
(4.3p) on turnover of Pounds 30.9m (Pounds 23.4m).
Abacus was the subject of a Pounds 3.4m management buy-out led by Mr Brian
Murdoch, its current managing director, and three colleagues in 1989.
