<HEADLINE>
FT  03 NOV 93 / World Trade News: Dubai plans Arabic TV service
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RAYMOND SNODDY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
EMIRATES Dubai Television plans to launch next month what it says is the
world's first 24-hour Arabic satellite television service.
EDTV, already available in the Middle East, hopes to reach 14m more Arabs
living in Europe and North and Central America.
The service will be carried on the Eutelsat II satellite in Europe and on
Galaxy satellite on the other side of the Atlantic, where it will be
available from Canada to Venezuela.
The exporting of a television service from Dubai is the latest sign of the
growing internationalising of the television market.
Next spring BBC World Service Television is to launch a news service in
Arabic for the Middle East. EDTV plans a December 6 launch.
EDTV, which will use programmes, presenters, and technical staff drawn from
all over the Middle East, plans to broadcast 70 per cent in Arabic and 30
per cent in English.
